# Documentation should be improved for batch actions · pocketbase/pocketbase · Discussion #6251
created: 2025-01-08, last updated: 2026-04-17, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/6251)

In the API preview for batch you are given this:
const batch = pb.createBatch();
batch.collection('transactions').create({ ... });
batch.collection('transactions').update('RECORD_ID', { ... });
batch.collection('transactions').delete('RECORD_ID');
batch.collection('transactions').upsert({ ... });
const result = await batch.send();
...
It is not how the batch web API work and it is not intended to be used this way.
The warnings and limits of the API are there are for a reason (*see also #6040*).
If you want to update every record in the collection you'll have to do it on the server-side using Go or JS pb_hooks but the description is too vague to help with anything more specific.

